<paragraph blockId="23.[264,1021,1155,1216]" box="[264,422,1190,1216]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
(
<figureCitation box="[273,414,1190,1216]" captionStart="FIGURES 47–49" captionStartId="24.[264,382,1478,1502]" captionTargetBox="[311,1269,622,1444]" captionTargetId="figure-244@24.[299,1289,612,1452]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 47–49. Chrysotimus songshanus sp. nov. (male). 47. Wing; 48. first flagellomere, lateral view; 49. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048691" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048691/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Figs. 47–49</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[264,1325,1270,1896]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Diagnosis. Four dc, acr absent. Hind tibia with 3 ad and 5–6 pd; fore tarsomere 1 with row of about 7–8 v; hind tarsomere 1 with 3–4 short black spine­like ventral bristles at base and row of 8–9 pv.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[264,1325,1270,1896]" box="[312,1157,1390,1416]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
Description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[463,533,1390,1416]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Male.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[692,836,1390,1416]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="1.85" valueMax="1.9" valueMin="1.8">1.8–1.9 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[994,1153,1390,1416]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.125" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="2.05" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="2.125" valueMax="2.2" valueMin="2.05">2.05–2.2 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[264,1325,1270,1896]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
Head metallic green with pale gray pollen; frons and face brilliant. Hairs and bristles on head yellow. Ocellar tubercle weak, with 2 very long oc and 2 very short posterior hairs. Lower postocular bristles (including ventral hairs) pale. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[1115,1200,1510,1536]" captionStart="FIGURES 47–49" captionStartId="24.[264,382,1478,1502]" captionTargetBox="[311,1269,622,1444]" captionTargetId="figure-244@24.[299,1289,612,1452]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 47–49. Chrysotimus songshanus sp. nov. (male). 47. Wing; 48. first flagellomere, lateral view; 49. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048691" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048691/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
) blackish; first flagellomere blackish, rather short, about 0.5 times as long as wide; arista sub­apical, with basal segment very short. Proboscis blackish, with brown hairs; palpus brown, with 2 yellow apical bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[264,1325,1270,1896]" lastBlockId="24.[264,1323,284,553]" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Thorax metallic green with pale gray pollen, mesonotum and scutellum brilliant. Hairs and bristles on thorax yellow; 4 strong dc, acr absent; scutellum with 2 pairs of bristles. Propleuron with 1 yellow hair on lower portion. Legs including coxae yellow with all tarsomere 5 brown. Hairs and bristles on legs yellow; coxae with yellowish hairs and bristles; fore coxa with 4 anterior and apical bristles, mid coxa with 2–3 anterior and apical bristles, hind coxa with 1 brown outer bristle near middle. Mid femur with 1 av apically, hind femur with 2 av and 1–2 pv apically. Mid tibia with 2 ad and 4 pd, apically with 3 bristles; hind tibia with 3 ad and 5–6 pd, apically with 4 bristles. Fore tarsomere 1 with row of about 7–8 v; hind tarsomere 1 with 3–4 short black spine­like ventral bristles at base, and row of 8–9 pv. Relative lengths of tibia and 5 tarsomeres of legs. LI 3.3: 1.9: 0.9: 0.8: 0.5: 0.5; LII 4.5: 2.6: 1.1: 0.8: 0.5: 0.4; LIII 5.3: 2.0: 1.3: 0.9: 0.6: 0.5.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[264,1323,284,553]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Wing hyaline (
<figureCitation box="[484,571,484,510]" captionStart="FIGURES 47–49" captionStartId="24.[264,382,1478,1502]" captionTargetBox="[311,1269,622,1444]" captionTargetId="figure-244@24.[299,1289,612,1452]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 47–49. Chrysotimus songshanus sp. nov. (male). 47. Wing; 48. first flagellomere, lateral view; 49. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048691" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048691/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
), veins brownish; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[806,836,496,513]" fontSize="7" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">4+5</subScript>
and M parallel apically, CuAx ratio 0.26. Squama yellow with pale yellow hairs. Halter yellow.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048691" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5048691" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048691/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" startId="24.[264,382,1478,1502]" targetBox="[311,1269,622,1444]" targetPageId="24">
<paragraph blockId="24.[264,1323,1478,1536]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,462,1478,1502]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">FIGURES 47–49.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Wang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2005" authorityName="Wang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2005" box="[468,733,1478,1501]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="songshanus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[468,733,1478,1501]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Chrysotimus songshanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[739,821,1478,1501]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(male). 47. Wing; 48. first flagellomere, lateral view; 49. genitalia, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="24.[264,1325,1627,1894]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Abdomen brown with pale gray pollen, dorsum dark brown. Hairs and bristles on abdomen yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[264,1325,1627,1894]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[502,593,1707,1733]" captionStart="FIGURES 47–49" captionStartId="24.[264,382,1478,1502]" captionTargetBox="[311,1269,622,1444]" captionTargetId="figure-244@24.[299,1289,612,1452]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 47–49. Chrysotimus songshanus sp. nov. (male). 47. Wing; 48. first flagellomere, lateral view; 49. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048691" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048691/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
). Epandrium distinctly longer than wide, apically with short lateral process; surstylus with short dorsal lobe, thick and curved ventral lobe; cercus somewhat round with moderate long hairs; aedeagus long and thick, with bifurcated apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[264,1325,1627,1894]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Female. Body length 
<quantity box="[568,712,1827,1853]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="1.95" valueMax="2.2" valueMin="1.7">1.7–2.2 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[875,1020,1827,1853]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.3" valueMin="2.2">2.2–2.3 mm</quantity>
. Similar to male, but fore tarsomere 1 without rowed v, and hind tarsomere 1 without black ventral bristles at base.
</paragraph>
