<paragraph blockId="25.[264,1324,284,590]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Comments. This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Yang and Saigusa" authorityName="Yang and Saigusa" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shennongjianus">
<emphasis box="[809,1149,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Chrysotimus shennongjianus</emphasis>
Yang and Saigusa
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[390,465,444,470]" country="China" name="Hubei" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Hubei</collectingRegion>
, but may be separated from the latter by the hind tibia with 3 ad, 5–6 pd, and fore tarsomere 1 with row of 7–8 v. In 
<taxonomicName box="[763,980,484,510]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shennongjianus">
<emphasis box="[763,782,484,509]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[796,980,484,509]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">shennongjianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the hind tibia has 2 ad, 2 pd, and fore tarsomere 1 has no distinct v (
<bibRefCitation author="Yang, D. &amp; Saigusa, T." box="[719,1021,524,550]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="155 - 164" refId="ref12011" refString="Yang, D. &amp; Saigusa, T. (2001 a) New and little known species of Dolichopodidae (Diptera) from China (VIII). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 71, 155 - 164." type="journal article" year="2001">Yang and Saigusa, 2001a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
